<br>
1) If you address ONLY the difference between AXE50 and AXE47, how much stronger do you think AXE50 is?  <br>
<br>
My initial guess is that the extra +3 axe is minimal, even wrt damage variance, so the primary benefit has to be the level 50 axe move right?  So what we really need is a single concise paragraph that compares Havoc/Tyr's Fury to Havoc/Havoc (or Evernight/Arctic Rift) plus the incremental damage from the level 44 shout.  For sake of argument, we can ignore the 46 dam add.<br>
<br>
2) Can you hit some Hibs and Albs using the 44 axe style arctic rift please.  Then post the numbers comparing arctic rift damage to Tyr's Fury?<br>
<br>
3) Do you find Havoc to be easy to set up?  I kept missing that Front position requirement so much I ended up giving into using Plague or Pillager all the time.<br>
<br>
4) Can you post your damage from Havoc and your damage from Tyr's Fury and damage from Pillager.  I just want to see, given all other variables are constant, how much more damage you are doing by being able to use Tyr's Fury whereas I would be limited to Havoc or Arctic Rift.  That will basically help make my decision.<br>
<br>
Question for all:<br>
<br>
1) Do any skalds care about the resist songs?  I find I use the 47 heat song a lot in RvR vs. Albs, and I use the Energy song a lot vs. Hib.  I was even thinking of going 48 BS for the Cold song.  Thoughts?  I have all my resists maxed at 26%, save for melee resists.  With str/con maxed, these resists cost me a lot of dex/quick. <p>-------------------------------------------------------------------
