<br>
Axe styles most commonly used in RvR hit harder than similar Hammer styles.<br>
<br>
Provoke is a low % style dmg, but costs very little endurance.  It also has a med defensive penalty <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
Lambast is fairly easy to chain with an OK parry skill, maybe once or twice a fight with a tank.  Harder to get reaction styles off with slow weapons though..keep that in mind.  Havoc, a front position style, does similar damage to Lambast, but can by styled easier in RvR, and can be chained without reaction (requires front only).  Lambast is also a low endurance style.<br>
<br>
Provoke/Lambast = low/med damage (low endurance)<br>
Havoc/Tyr's = med/high damage (med-high endurance)<br>
provoke will make up most of the hits however, Tyr's is much easier to get off.  So the damage shifts even higher Axe if you choose provoke. <br>
<br>
In general, if endurance isnt' a concern, Axes give you more up front damage.  Quite a bit more.  Anywhere from (edit, # not exact) 30-60 per hit depending on which styles you're comparing.  Two melee swings and you're already up 120 damage.  Damage add is about 8 points or so per swing given damage like that.  The DDs are not going to catch up to that until they run out of endurance, I'd wager.<br>
<br>
I think it follows that:<br>
44 spec vs 50 spec, when modified with RAs, will still be a small gain in overall damage.<br>
<br>
However, compare 44 hammer to 50 axe, you're increasing damage through STYLES, but at a cost of endurance.<br>
<br>
Increasing from 44 hammer to 50 hammer still doesn't seem to be a good tradeoff when you take everything into account.   So new tests IMO should simply focus on:<br>
<br>
% style damage for hammer/axe/sword.<br>
Endurance usage of each style.<br>
<br>
We have a lot of style % data floating around.  I think we're really short on endurance data.<br>
<br>
-Dane <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dane>Dane</A> at: 9/10/02 3:06:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uaurensirramalot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AurenSirRamAlot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/19/02 11:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=284.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 Hammer vs 44 Hammer Template</span><hr size=1> Might i make a suggestion in the future?<br>
